    <text id="B1071T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson informs Carson that a Joseph Harrison claims Carson owes him $41 plus
                    interest.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen, and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Office 4th <abbr expan="Division">Div.</abbr> 9 <abbr
                            expan="Sub-District">Sub Dist</abbr><abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr James E. Carson<lb/>Middlebrook</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-07-05"><abbr expan="July 5, 1867">July 5/67</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>A claim against you on behalf of Joseph Harrison (<abbr expan="colored">c</abbr>)
                    for $41 00/100 with Interest from June 1st 1866 is lodged in this office and I
                    call your attention to the necessity of an early settlement. You will make some
                    arrangement or explanation to me by the 13t Instant.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr. obt. servt</abbr>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>Thos P. Jackson<lb/>Agent</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
